1
00:00:54,550 --> 00:00:56,040
Mr. No.

2
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:59,230
Please help me this time.

3
00:00:59,230 --> 00:01:01,970
I beg of you. Please.

4
00:01:02,810 --> 00:01:04,970
My mom went through surgery.

5
00:01:04,970 --> 00:01:07,220
If you can adjust my dispatch schedule this week,

6
00:01:07,220 --> 00:01:09,750
I'll work without any days off.

7
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:11,500
I'll tally the deposits, too.

8
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:14,900
- I'm good at math and abacus-
- Geez, forget it!

9
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:16,600
I don't need any of that.

10
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:20,200
We're short on attendants as it is.

11
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:23,660
- Manager No, please-
- Manager or not, I said no!

12
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:24,950
Think about it.

13
00:01:24,950 --> 00:01:26,890
If I listen to everyone's situation,

14
00:01:26,890 --> 00:01:29,710
do you think I can run the company or not?

15
00:01:29,710 --> 00:01:31,500
If you insist on making a hole* on the schedule,
(Not showing up for work)

16
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,710
just quit. Clean and simple.

17
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:39,070
The only hole around here is in your sock.

18
00:01:39,070 --> 00:01:41,430
Who'll stitch up that hole in your sock, Mr. No?

19
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:43,480
Your elderly mother will, right?

20
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:45,370
Since you couldn't get married all this time.

21
00:01:45,370 --> 00:01:47,250
Be quiet if you're not going
to stitch it up for me.

22
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:51,500
They opened up her mother's stomach
and performed surgery on her.

23
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:55,510
How could you deny her without hesitation?
You're too cruel.

24
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:58,100
We'll cover Yeong Rye's dispatch.

25
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,640
That works, right?

26
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,360
Girls...

27
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:06,840
You girls are being ridiculous.

28
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:12,090
What a loyal lot of friends you are!

29
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:13,930
But that's too bad.

30
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:17,740
You two aren't enough to cover her.

31
00:02:17,740 --> 00:02:21,920
Do you think I'd accept your request or not? Huh?

32
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:25,390
Ms. Ko, you think I'd accept it or not?

33
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:28,880
Then, I'll cover her, too.

34
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:36,260
I think the three of us will be
enough to cover her dispatches.

35
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:38,200
Jong Hui.

36
00:02:45,690 --> 00:02:49,780
Aren't you guys all pushing it
too hard because of me?

37
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:52,780
It's going to be tough without any days off.

38
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:56,350
What? Among us? What are friends for?

39
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:58,850
I'm about to feel hurt.

40
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:01,740
She's right. To put it bluntly,

41
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:06,750
wouldn't you help us out
if we were in your situation?

42
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:10,070
Yeah. We all have to help each other out.

43
00:03:10,070 --> 00:03:11,630
Right?

44
00:03:15,580 --> 00:03:18,520
Anyway, how long will they be like that?

45
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:21,050
They're making us uncomfortable, too.

46
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,770
All over a gigolo.

47
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:32,220
A friendship thinner than
tissue paper just ripped apart.

48
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:34,550
Exactly.

49
00:03:34,550 --> 00:03:38,520
They used to be glued together. Really.

50
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:40,400
I don't get it, either.

51
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:44,800
There's a sea of men out there.
Must they be like that?

52
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,780
 Here. 

53
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:12,420
 Can you give this to Seo Jong Hui? 

54
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:32,150
 

55
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:34,500
 

56
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:38,050
Stupid. Idiot. Dumbass.

57
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:39,800
Loser. Fool-

58
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:42,900
That won't do it. You have to slam it harder.

59
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:48,830
Hey. If I find a time machine,

60
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:51,400
I'd go back to the event match without hesitation.

61
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:55,820
I'd block Deok Goo's moves in advance
and knock him out with an uppercut.

62
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:57,450
Then, Yeong Rye would say,

63
00:04:57,450 --> 00:05:00,790
"Oh, Sang Cheol. You're so manly and cool.

64
00:05:00,790 --> 00:05:02,950
I've fallen head over heels for you."

65
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:04,470
Right?

66
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,970
Crazy bastard.

67
00:05:09,970 --> 00:05:13,230
Right. I look crazy to you, too, right?

68
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:19,250
Gosh, what's wrong with me?

69
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:21,370
Now that I think it's over,

70
00:05:21,370 --> 00:05:24,690
I feel more regretful and miss her more.

71
00:05:24,690 --> 00:05:28,260
Then, why don't you visit her at the hospital?

72
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:31,140
Hospital? Visit who?

73
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,210
Aigoo, what a nuisance.

74
00:05:41,210 --> 00:05:44,150
I told you to go.

75
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:46,880
Aigoo, you're so stubborn.

76
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,770
I haven't seen anyone more stubborn than you.

77
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:50,530
It's fine.

78
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:54,520
My coworkers said they'll cover me at work.

79
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:59,600
Hey. Then, at least stop by home.

80
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,530
See what the kids are up to,

81
00:06:01,530 --> 00:06:05,530
do the laundry, and make a few side dishes.

82
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:08,490
Yeong Sik can't handle it on his own.

83
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:12,300
He already has his plate full
with studying and tutoring.

84
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:16,240
You're only worried about Oppa
even in this situation?

85
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:19,360
Of course. He's the pillar of our family.

86
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,150
Then, what am I?

87
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:22,900
You're...

88
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:26,730
my daughter. My eldest daughter.

89
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,820
Right.

90
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:33,170
I'm the eldest daughter.

91
00:06:33,170 --> 00:06:36,840
One who must earn money and
look after her younger siblings.

92
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,870
Even my mom treats me like this.

93
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:41,290
Who would consider me precious and like me, right?

94
00:06:41,290 --> 00:06:43,290
Look at this girl.

95
00:06:43,290 --> 00:06:46,570
Did you swallow a pickaxe today?

96
00:06:46,570 --> 00:06:48,530
Why are your words so spikey?

97
00:06:48,530 --> 00:06:50,710
I don't know.

98
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:54,240
I can't help how my words are coming out today.

99
00:06:56,570 --> 00:06:58,210
The pillar is here.

100
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:01,430
I'll go to take care of the kids, do laundry,
and make side dishes.

101
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:03,750
You look after Mom, Mr. Pillar.

102
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:06,110
Don't eat the entire can of peaches.

103
00:07:06,110 --> 00:07:08,160
Feed Mom, too.

104
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:13,170
- What's up with her?
- I don't know.

105
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:15,270
I wonder if something's going on at work.

106
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:17,040
Stomp, stomp, stomp!

107
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:20,740
 Get clean. Get clean. 

108
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:23,000
- Jong Hui, I'm good at this, right?
- Yeah.

109
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,890
- I'm good too, right?
- The best! Work harder!

110
00:07:24,890 --> 00:07:26,700
Jong Hui.

111
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,440
- Unni!
- Noona!

112
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,260
You're here.

113
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:33,630
What brings you here without a word?

114
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,010
When did you get here?

115
00:07:35,010 --> 00:07:36,650
A little bit ago.

116
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,270
Over there.

117
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:43,500
You couldn't attend class last night.

118
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,230
You know I don't usually take notes, right?

119
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:49,660
I wrote away with the pen you gifted me.

120
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:53,270
Don't complain if you see
a few worms here and there.

121
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:55,870
I did my best to stay awake.

122
00:07:55,870 --> 00:07:59,440
Stomp! Stomp!

123
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:04,320
What are you doing? We have to feed the kids.

124
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,810
Right? They're probably really
hungry after all this labor.

125
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:11,110
- Right? You're hungry, right?
 - Yes! 

126
00:08:11,110 --> 00:08:14,940
All right. I'll whip something up.

127
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:41,750
I love your flower bed.

128
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,150
The flowers are pretty

129
00:08:44,150 --> 00:08:46,690
and the vegetable garden is nice, too.

130
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:57,320
Your mother is feeling all better, right?

131
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,860
Yeah.

132
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:04,690
But I'm not letting her get discharged
until she's fully recovered.

133
00:09:04,690 --> 00:09:06,970
She might insist on working right away.

134
00:09:06,970 --> 00:09:11,150
Yeah. I think your mother is more
than willing to do that.

135
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:13,800
You don't know how shocked I was
when I heard she underwent surgery.

136
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,790
The sky turned yellow.

137
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:18,170
That should never happen again.

138
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:21,540
Here.

139
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:33,440
J-Jong Hui.

140
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,810
Yeah?

141
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:45,000
Here.

142
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,510
What's that?

143
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,020
On the day Mom collapsed,

144
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:57,080
I ran into Han Jae Pil on the street.

145
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,740
Han Jae Pil?

146
00:09:59,610 --> 00:10:01,060
 

147
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:02,620
Oh, yeah.

148
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:05,710
I was frantically trying to catch a taxi

149
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:08,500
when he showed up and gave us
a ride to the hospital.

150
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,430
- With his family's car.
- Really?

151
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:13,380
How grateful.

152
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:22,020
He asked me to give that to you.

153
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:24,300
- Me?
- Yeah.

154
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:29,660
You know how they invited us to the boxing gym?

155
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:32,190
It must've been because of you.

156
00:10:32,190 --> 00:10:34,700
I didn't even realize that

157
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:38,840
and counted my chickens before they hatched.

158
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,950
Really?

159
00:10:40,950 --> 00:10:43,020
What a funny guy.

160
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:45,650
I don't know about funny.

161
00:10:46,940 --> 00:10:51,340
Anyway, I gave it to you.

162
00:10:51,340 --> 00:10:53,010
Mission complete.

163
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,140
And you?

164
00:10:56,140 --> 00:10:58,650
Weren't you interested in him, too?

165
00:10:58,650 --> 00:11:00,670
Me?

166
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:04,700
No. I thought he was interested in me.

167
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:08,610
So I considered giving him a chance. That's all.

168
00:11:08,610 --> 00:11:10,400
I don't like him.

169
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:13,140
He's not even my type.

170
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,650
Really?

171
00:11:39,050 --> 00:11:41,190
Why?

172
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:43,400
You don't like him?

173
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:46,030
Like or not.

174
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:48,460
I'm not interested in dating.

175
00:11:48,460 --> 00:11:50,590
Nor can I afford to.

176
00:11:51,690 --> 00:11:53,340
And...

177
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:59,250
he doesn't know anything about me.

178
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:05,960
I'll go get more chips.

179
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,760
You want some, too, right?

180
00:12:21,090 --> 00:12:22,340
Really?

181
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:24,860
You met her on the street? Randomly?

182
00:12:24,860 --> 00:12:26,800
Yeah.

183
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,720
That should've been me!

184
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:32,140
I should've given her a ride even if
I had to borrow the rice store's truck.

185
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,960
Should I pay a visit?

186
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,390
Go ahead.

187
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:37,200
I don't know if she'll welcome you, though.

188
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,370
Hey, let's go together.

189
00:12:39,370 --> 00:12:42,330
At least, you have a reason
since you gave her a ride.

190
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:44,760
I have a reason,

191
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:47,820
but I don't need to go out of my way-

192
00:12:48,850 --> 00:12:51,380
Out of your... What?

193
00:12:55,990 --> 00:12:57,780
Let's go.

194
00:12:57,780 --> 00:12:59,630
Let's go. I'll go with you.

195
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:01,860
Really? Really? Really?

196
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:04,240
My heart is racing.

197
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:06,170
Should we buy something? Flowers? Fruits?

198
00:13:06,170 --> 00:13:09,470
Hey. I'm hiccoughing. Look! Hey, hey.

199
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:14,970
Hi.

200
00:13:14,970 --> 00:13:17,290
H-Hi.

201
00:13:17,290 --> 00:13:18,880
Hi.

202
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:26,590
Well, I heard from Jae Pil.

203
00:13:26,590 --> 00:13:29,120
It's one thing if I didn't know.
But now that I know,

204
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:31,500
I felt it was my duty as your friend.

205
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,690
Of course, we can't say we're friends
or we're not friends.

206
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:37,850
Our relationship is difficult to label.

207
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,790
What, Jae Pil?

208
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:43,510
He thought you might be sick of hospital food.

209
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:44,510
Yeah.

210
00:13:44,510 --> 00:13:47,480
Sang Cheol's parents run a store at the market.

211
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:50,640
Yeah. A small restaurant.

212
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:52,990
But it's somewhat big for a market stall.

213
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:55,390
They sell salted and pickled foods.

214
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:56,870
It's surprisingly lucrative.

215
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:58,430
I'm not bragging,

216
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:01,580
but the neighbors all say we're the real deal.

217
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:03,530
They love it.

218
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,850
O-Oh! H-Here you go.

219
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:14,540
- Thanks. We'll enjoy it.
- Sure.

220
00:14:18,940 --> 00:14:22,260
How's your mother feeling? Is she better?

221
00:14:22,260 --> 00:14:24,470
Yes, thanks to you.

222
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:27,610
As a matter of fact, she asked who gave us a ride

223
00:14:27,610 --> 00:14:30,490
- and said she's grateful.
- Oh, no.

224
00:14:30,490 --> 00:14:32,430
Of course, a ride is given.

225
00:14:36,610 --> 00:14:38,170
Hey.

226
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:41,700
Can I talk to you?

227
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:47,690
Huh?

228
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:05,030
Hey.

229
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,280
Yeah?

230
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:10,440
The note I gave you last time.

231
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:13,450
Yeah.

232
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:18,250
You gave it to her, right? What did she say?

233
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,130
Well...

234
00:15:21,020 --> 00:15:26,710
I don't think Jong Hui wants to date
anyone at the moment.

235
00:15:26,710 --> 00:15:29,250
Oh, really?

236
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:32,720
Then, why did she join the meeting?

237
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:35,610
Was it just for fun?

238
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:38,180
Well, that's understandable.

239
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:40,220
Understandable.

240
00:15:40,220 --> 00:15:42,070
Sorry for the trouble.

241
00:15:42,070 --> 00:15:44,980
You've got your hands full with
your mother being sick. I feel bad.

242
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:48,650
No. No, it's fine. It's okay...

243
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:56,410
You made all that fuss,
saying you weren't interested.

244
00:15:56,410 --> 00:15:57,700
Acting stone-faced.

245
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:58,870
That's enough.

246
00:15:58,870 --> 00:16:00,750
A total wolf in sheep's clothing, huh?

247
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:02,430
Awoo!

248
00:16:02,430 --> 00:16:05,330
I said, enough. Say one more word.

249
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:07,930
When did you fall for her?

250
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:11,290
When Jong Hui took off her
jacket at the skating rink?

251
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:13,370
Or when she yelled out "Stop"?

252
00:16:14,350 --> 00:16:17,000
Was it love at first sight?

253
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:20,060
Wow, you were giving me crap
when I was thinking about Yeong Rye.

254
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:22,330
But you stayed up all night
thinking about Jong Hui.

255
00:16:22,330 --> 00:16:23,780
That's what happened!

256
00:16:23,780 --> 00:16:26,580
- All right! I'll stop!
- I said that was enough.

257
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:28,520
Hyung! Hyung! I'll stop.

258
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:30,280
I'll stop. All right, I'll stop.

259
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,520
What's wrong with you?

260
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:34,430
Hey, Jae Pil. Tell me anything you want to eat.

261
00:16:34,430 --> 00:16:37,230
I'll treat you in consolation
for being completely rejected!

262
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:38,930
I'll treat you! It's my treat!

263
00:16:38,930 --> 00:16:42,100
I said I'll treat you!
What's the problem? My treat!

264
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,760
Oh, when did you get here?

265
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:38,960
You must not be the sensitive type.
Sleeping anywhere like that.

266
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:40,360
I'm sensitive.

