- Put some on your hands, too.
- Forget it!

807
00:59:55,820 --> 00:59:58,610
- Come here.
- I'm old, anyway.

808
01:00:10,840 --> 01:00:12,570
Yeong Mi.

809
01:00:12,570 --> 01:00:13,650
Yeah?

810
01:00:13,650 --> 01:00:16,760
Do you think my face looks paler?

811
01:00:17,880 --> 01:00:21,030
No, it looks the same. Like a sweet potato.

812
01:00:22,080 --> 01:00:23,250
- Oppa.
- Yeah?

813
01:00:23,250 --> 01:00:26,690
That omurice was delicious, right?

814
01:00:26,690 --> 01:00:29,200
It was yellow and really soft.

815
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:30,450
It was delicious.

816
01:00:30,450 --> 01:00:32,000
There was meat in it, too.

817
01:00:32,000 --> 01:00:33,020
There was.

818
01:00:33,020 --> 01:00:34,540
Don't you want to eat it again?

819
01:00:34,540 --> 01:00:36,230
I do.

820
01:00:37,280 --> 01:00:41,180
Se Ri said we could come over again.

821
01:00:49,560 --> 01:00:52,950
Oh, my! What brings you two here again?

822
01:00:52,950 --> 01:00:54,490
- Hello.
- Hello.

823
01:00:54,490 --> 01:00:56,760
Se Ri said to come over again.

824
01:00:56,760 --> 01:00:58,490
I see.

825
01:00:58,490 --> 01:01:00,040
And that is...

826
01:01:00,040 --> 01:01:05,580
Mom said we shouldn't go to
people's houses empty-handed.

827
01:01:06,540 --> 01:01:08,490
- Here you go.
- Oh, sure.

828
01:01:08,490 --> 01:01:09,930
Gosh.

829
01:01:09,930 --> 01:01:12,840
Take your shoes off and go in.

830
01:01:12,840 --> 01:01:14,260
Yeong Bae! Yeong Mi!

831
01:01:14,260 --> 01:01:15,770
Unni!

832
01:01:16,480 --> 01:01:18,100
Hi.

833
01:01:19,060 --> 01:01:23,400
Whoa. It's the pumpkin from Cinderella!

834
01:01:31,820 --> 01:01:33,810
You said you saw her, you bastard.

835
01:01:33,810 --> 01:01:35,640
When and where did you see her?

836
01:01:35,640 --> 01:01:37,930
I saw her at Yeonpung Intersection,

837
01:01:37,930 --> 01:01:40,300
but I was so wasted, too.

838
01:01:40,300 --> 01:01:43,020
- I couldn't see the bus number.
- You bastard.

839
01:01:43,020 --> 01:01:45,940
I was unsure because of the attendant's uniform,

840
01:01:45,940 --> 01:01:50,030
but it was your sister for sure!

841
01:01:52,410 --> 01:01:54,190
Attendant uniform?

842
01:01:55,250 --> 01:01:57,730
That bitch is a bus attendant?

843
01:02:38,940 --> 01:02:41,500
Try to run all you want.

844
01:03:15,880 --> 01:03:19,070
- Hey!
- Unni!

845
01:03:19,070 --> 01:03:21,340
Hey!

846
01:03:23,720 --> 01:03:27,660
It feels like it's been ages
when it's only been a few days.

847
01:03:27,660 --> 01:03:30,110
I almost forgot your face!

848
01:03:30,110 --> 01:03:31,710
Have you been well?

849
01:03:31,710 --> 01:03:34,400
I gave you all a tough time, didn't I?

850
01:03:34,400 --> 01:03:36,400
Hey, Ko Yeong Rye.

851
01:03:36,400 --> 01:03:38,420
It's been a while.

852
01:03:45,280 --> 01:03:47,090
Cheers!

853
01:03:51,860 --> 01:03:53,700
Wait, I got you.

854
01:03:56,270 --> 01:03:58,330
Here. Go ahead.

855
01:04:02,500 --> 01:04:05,280
One would think you're the patient.

856
01:04:05,280 --> 01:04:07,340
You lost even more weight.

857
01:04:08,250 --> 01:04:11,390
I did try to eat properly.

858
01:04:11,390 --> 01:04:14,120
Have more after you're done. I'll make more.

859
01:04:17,070 --> 01:04:19,530
Here. This is for dessert.

860
01:04:19,530 --> 01:04:21,170
Thank you.

861
01:04:27,600 --> 01:04:30,170
I met that guy yesterday. Han Jae Pil.

862
01:04:32,420 --> 01:04:35,910
He must've found out I'm a regular at Vivaldi.

863
01:04:35,910 --> 01:04:37,990
He was waiting there.

864
01:04:40,260 --> 01:04:42,040
He said it was his birthday, so we ate together

865
01:04:42,040 --> 01:04:44,610
and we went to the department
store to get him a gift.

866
01:04:44,610 --> 01:04:46,860
You know Dongin Department Store?

867
01:04:46,860 --> 01:04:49,090
He's the son of that family.

868
01:04:49,090 --> 01:04:51,790
He saw his father and hid.

869
01:04:51,790 --> 01:04:53,970
His father must be a bit violent.

870
01:04:53,970 --> 01:04:56,080
And his mom passed away.

871
01:04:56,990 --> 01:05:00,350
I realized being rich doesn't make you happy.

872
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:05,800
He gave me his number again.

873
01:05:05,800 --> 01:05:08,400
To go to the library together this weekend.

874
01:05:16,650 --> 01:05:18,360
And?

875
01:05:19,700 --> 01:05:21,480
How do you feel?

876
01:05:21,480 --> 01:05:23,180
Huh?

877
01:05:23,180 --> 01:05:27,700
You're still not interested in him?

878
01:05:28,660 --> 01:05:30,280
At all?

879
01:05:30,280 --> 01:05:32,500
I'm not sure.

880
01:05:34,630 --> 01:05:36,500
It's strange.

881
01:05:38,040 --> 01:05:41,110
He seems very well off.

882
01:05:41,110 --> 01:05:45,280
But at the same time, he seems
deprived and lonely, too.

883
01:05:47,810 --> 01:05:50,790
He has been on my mind. Oddly.

884
01:05:56,520 --> 01:05:59,060
Then, why don't you try seeing him?

885
01:05:59,060 --> 01:06:01,820
A guy who asked me out to the library?

886
01:06:01,820 --> 01:06:04,070
No, I don't want to.

887
01:06:11,930 --> 01:06:15,160
He doesn't know me that well

888
01:06:15,160 --> 01:06:18,510
and I can't be honest with him.

889
01:06:18,510 --> 01:06:20,680
I don't like those two facts.

890
01:06:27,570 --> 01:06:33,330
Don't you think it's because
you developed feelings for him?

891
01:06:33,330 --> 01:06:36,500
Or you wouldn't even be upset.

892
01:06:38,390 --> 01:06:40,290
Is that it?

893
01:06:46,200 --> 01:06:48,890
I don't know my own feelings, either.

894
01:06:51,020 --> 01:06:53,700
But one thing for sure

895
01:06:53,700 --> 01:06:57,060
is that we should meet again.

896
01:06:57,060 --> 01:07:00,030
I should be honest with him for starters.

897
01:07:00,030 --> 01:07:03,480
That I'm an attendant and not a day student.

898
01:07:04,530 --> 01:07:07,730
I'll think about what happens after that later.

899
01:07:07,730 --> 01:07:11,410
In the end, it's either we date
or we don't, right?

900
01:07:16,780 --> 01:07:19,290
But I have a full bus schedule that day.

901
01:07:20,610 --> 01:07:23,170
I guess I didn't have time anyway.

902
01:07:33,040 --> 01:07:36,190
I'll cover you.

903
01:07:39,620 --> 01:07:42,220
You filled in for me, too.

904
01:07:42,220 --> 01:07:44,320
- Really?
- Yeah.

905
01:07:45,470 --> 01:07:47,580
You'd do that for me?

906
01:07:47,580 --> 01:07:48,960
Yeah.

907
01:07:54,870 --> 01:07:56,420
Okay.

908
01:07:57,580 --> 01:07:59,120
Then...

909
01:08:00,610 --> 01:08:02,560
I'll give him a call right now.

910
01:08:02,560 --> 01:08:05,830
- Finish up and start cleaning.
- Okay.

911
01:08:38,750 --> 01:08:41,200
 Yes, hello? 

912
01:08:46,190 --> 01:08:47,960
 Hello? 

913
01:08:53,700 --> 01:08:55,230
Hello?

914
01:08:55,230 --> 01:08:57,730
You should speak if you called.

915
01:08:57,730 --> 01:09:00,760
Who are you? Who are you, you punk?

916
01:09:00,760 --> 01:09:03,670
You little brat. How dare you prank call me?

917
01:09:03,670 --> 01:09:05,360
Who the hell are you?

918
01:09:07,240 --> 01:09:08,920
That little...

919
01:09:10,730 --> 01:09:14,800
Kids like that should be picked up
and thrown into jail.

920
01:09:15,660 --> 01:09:18,230
Our nation's legal system is too weak.

921
01:09:35,280 --> 01:09:36,530
Hello?

922
01:09:36,530 --> 01:09:38,780
Hey.

923
01:09:38,780 --> 01:09:41,460
It's me, Seo Jong Hui.

924
01:09:41,460 --> 01:09:44,540
Yeah. Huh?

925
01:09:44,540 --> 01:09:47,500
I'm using a public phone,
and I only have 10 won left.

926
01:09:47,500 --> 01:09:50,490
I'll get straight to the point, so listen up.

927
01:09:50,490 --> 01:09:51,520
Okay.

928
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:54,170
 Meet me in front of Vivaldi on Sunday at 1 p.m. 

929
01:09:54,170 --> 01:09:56,850
I need to tell you something first.

930
01:09:58,600 --> 01:10:01,940
Not over the phone.

931
01:10:03,760 --> 01:10:05,470
 Yes. 

932
01:10:05,470 --> 01:10:09,210
 It was bound to end up this way anyway. 

933
01:10:10,320 --> 01:10:14,370
 Your one encounter was
a stronger and more powerful fate 

934
01:10:14,370 --> 01:10:18,330
 than my three fateful meetings. 

935
01:10:21,460 --> 01:10:27,940
 That's why I think I'll retract my right
to pursue happiness. 

936
01:10:27,940 --> 01:10:29,660
 Because... 

937
01:10:36,870 --> 01:10:42,430
 you have the right to pursue
your happiness as well. 

938
01:10:42,430 --> 01:10:44,620
 And... 

939
01:10:44,620 --> 01:10:49,510
 the person I wish happiness for after myself, 

940
01:10:52,740 --> 01:10:55,970
 is you. 

941
01:11:18,750 --> 01:11:20,220
Here.

942
01:11:34,460 --> 01:11:36,050
Oh, that's good.

943
01:11:36,050 --> 01:11:37,750
Why the pumpkin porridge?

944
01:11:37,750 --> 01:11:39,890
The tutor's younger siblings brought it.

945
01:11:39,890 --> 01:11:41,160
- Siblings?
- Yeah.

946
01:11:41,160 --> 01:11:43,960
His brother is around Se Ri's age

947
01:11:43,960 --> 01:11:46,420
and the girl is a year or two younger.

948
01:11:46,420 --> 01:11:48,590
Mr. Ko must be the eldest son.

949
01:11:48,590 --> 01:11:50,480
His father passed away early-

950
01:11:50,480 --> 01:11:52,300
There you go again.

951
01:11:52,300 --> 01:11:55,930
Why are you so interested in
other people's family matters?

952
01:11:55,930 --> 01:11:57,730
Not exactly that... Se Ri, come here.

953
01:11:57,730 --> 01:11:59,980
- Se Ri, sit down.
- Sit.

954
01:12:00,970 --> 01:12:02,030
- Have some porridge.
- Good girl.

955
01:12:02,030 --> 01:12:04,360
It's hot, so make sure to cool it down.

956
01:12:04,360 --> 01:12:05,740
Okay!

957
01:12:11,970 --> 01:12:13,810
Is it good?

958
01:12:13,810 --> 01:12:15,920
- By the way, Mom.
- Yeah.

959
01:12:15,920 --> 01:12:18,390
Where's my Cinderella pumpkin?

960
01:12:18,390 --> 01:12:21,600
I left it there, but it disappeared.

961
01:12:21,600 --> 01:12:23,110
I want to leave it in my room.

962
01:12:23,110 --> 01:12:26,680
That? I made porridge with it.

963
01:12:26,680 --> 01:12:29,330
You just had a spoonful.

964
01:12:31,280 --> 01:12:33,860
- Give me one more bowl.
- Okay.

965
01:12:38,500 --> 01:12:41,590
Give me my Cinderella pumpkin! Why did you eat it?

966
01:12:41,590 --> 01:12:44,040
- I'm leaving.
- I have to turn it into a carriage!

967
01:12:44,040 --> 01:12:45,460
Have some porridge!

968
01:12:45,460 --> 01:12:47,700
It's Saturday, so there's no lunch.

969
01:12:47,700 --> 01:12:51,990
- It's fine. I'm off.
- My Cinderella pumpkin!

970
01:12:57,700 --> 01:12:59,380
You're done already?

971
01:12:59,380 --> 01:13:00,820
That was fast.

972
01:13:00,820 --> 01:13:05,170
Yeah. Maybe because it's Saturday.
It's a bit quiet.

973
01:13:12,200 --> 01:13:13,580
What?

974
01:13:13,580 --> 01:13:16,850
No reason. You're just pretty.

975
01:13:17,740 --> 01:13:21,980
Right, I'm the beauty at Cheongah Transportation.

976
01:13:23,400 --> 01:13:27,290
You really are pretty. Even now.

977
01:13:32,600 --> 01:13:37,260
So, you'll tell him tomorrow, right?

978
01:13:37,260 --> 01:13:38,990
I should.

979
01:13:40,130 --> 01:13:41,960
I'm off!

980
01:13:51,790 --> 01:13:54,610
Jong Hui! Jong Hui!

981
01:13:54,610 --> 01:13:58,850
Seo Jong Hui! She left her beret behind.

982
01:13:58,850 --> 01:14:00,800
If an inspector from HQ catches her,

983
01:14:00,800 --> 01:14:04,060
she'll get in trouble for improper uniform.

984
01:14:04,060 --> 01:14:07,210
- Give it to me. I'll run after her.
- What?

985
01:14:07,210 --> 01:14:10,930
How are you going to catch
a bus that's already left?

986
01:14:41,330 --> 01:14:43,760
Are you all right? Is anyone hurt?

987
01:14:43,760 --> 01:14:46,010
Aigoo. I'm sorry.

988
01:14:46,010 --> 01:14:49,180
The tire suddenly got a flat.

989
01:14:49,180 --> 01:14:53,110
I think you'll have to get off
and take the next bus.

990
01:14:53,110 --> 01:14:55,200
Sorry!

991
01:14:55,200 --> 01:14:56,320
Please get off.

992
01:14:56,320 --> 01:14:57,540
We're sorry.

993
01:14:57,540 --> 01:14:59,010
Please get off. Sorry.

994
01:14:59,010 --> 01:15:01,080
Geez.

995
01:15:01,080 --> 01:15:02,420
That was a close one.

996
01:15:02,420 --> 01:15:04,770
We're sorry.

997
01:15:04,770 --> 01:15:06,550
Sorry.

998
01:15:07,530 --> 01:15:09,490
Sorry.

999
01:15:31,680 --> 01:15:35,150
Gosh. It's cleaning duty again if I'm late.

1000
01:15:35,150 --> 01:15:38,540
Will it be faster to get on the next one

1001
01:15:38,540 --> 01:15:40,920
and make a transfer?

